item.title: CVE-2014-0242|2024-08-06T09:05:39.434Z -- mod_wsgi -- mod_wsgi
item.description: mod_wsgi module before 3.4 for Apache, when used in embedded mode, might allow remote attackers to obtain sensitive information via the Content-Type header which is generated from memory that may have been freed and then overwritten by a separate thread.
